Kubernetes (K8s) is an open-source platform used to automate the deployment, scaling, and management of containerized applications.

Here are a few simple lines:

Kubernetes helps manage containers across multiple servers efficiently.
It automates tasks such as application deployment, scaling, load balancing, and recovery from failures.
Kubernetes works well with container platforms such as Docker.
It ensures high availability by automatically restarting failed containers and distributing workloads.
Kubernetes is widely used in cloud computing, microservices, and DevOps environments.
It supports deployment on on-premises infrastructure as well as cloud platforms.
Major cloud providers offer managed Kubernetes services for easier administration.

In one sentence: Kubernetes is a container orchestration platform that automates the deployment, scaling, and management of containerized applications.
